Durban — For tourists who are going to be visiting Ladysmith after the relaunch of the Battlefields Festival, Dongala Boutique Hotel is their best bet. The hotel, in the heart of Ladysmith, offers a 4-star experience which is more like a 5-star experience, with their welcoming start which ensures that you are comfortable all the time. At Dongala Boutique Hotel you are guaranteed to enjoy a peaceful breakaway close to game reserves, a variety of things to do and interesting activities. The hotel conveys elegance at its finest, as is known for hosting weddings, birthday celebrations, anniversaries and other functions. The hotel caters to everything and everyone, and works to your budget. The hotel has also hosted President Cyril Ramaphosa. With great views of the surrounding scenery, the hotel offers many ways to relax. You can simply chill outside watching the day unfold or chilling by the pool. The hotel offers all of the comfort in the world. The accommodation offerings differ, from the Group Chalet, which has four bedrooms, each with a double bed and a small en-suite bathroom with a shower. This chalet is a shared living area. They also have a presidential suite that has a kitchenette, a master bedroom and a private bathroom, along with a living area and a large private patio. They also have “queen rooms”, which have a queen-size bed, an en-suite bathroom and a private patio. Breakfast is complementary and you can also enjoy dinner in their inside restaurant. Daily News